{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-readme-js","path":"/stingalleman/awesome-audiovisual/readme/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"c39856b9-1aeb-52e6-91bf-980f6f24b642","html":"<h1 id=\"awesome-audiovisual-awesome\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#awesome-audiovisual-awesome\" aria-label=\"awesome audiovisual awesome permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Awesome Audiovisual <a href=\"https://awesome.re\"><img src=\"https://awesome.re/badge.svg\" alt=\"Awesome\"></a></h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Curated list of software, libraries and resources for lighting, video and audio professionals and hobbyists.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Want to add something? Just make a pull request, but be sure to follow the <a href=\"https://github.com/stingalleman/awesome-audiovisual/blob/main/contributing.md\">contributing guidelines</a>! Question? Ask it in the <a href=\"https://github.com/stingalleman/awesome-audiovisual/issues/2\">General Discussion issue</a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"contents\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#contents\" aria-label=\"contents permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Contents</h2>\n<!--lint ignore awesome-toc --><html><head></head><body>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#Lighting\">Lighting</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#Lighting-Software\">Lighting Software</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Visualizer\">Visualizers</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"#Audio\">Audio</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#Audio-Software\">Audio Software</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Audio-tools\">Audio tools</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"#Video\">Video</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#Video-Software\">Video Software</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Playout-And-Switching\">Playout And Switching</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Control-and-Orchestration\">Control and Orchestration</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Projection-Mapping\">Projection Mapping</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Protocols\">Protocols</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Video-Tools\">Video Tools</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"#Tools\">Tools</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#CADs\">CADs</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Timecode\">Timecode</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Monitoring\">Monitoring</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"#Libraries-and-frameworks\">Libraries and frameworks</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#ArtNet-Libraries\">ArtNet Libraries</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"#Hardware\">Hardware</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Graphics\">Graphics</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#Resources\">Resources</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#Blogs\">Blogs</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"#Tutorials\">Tutorials</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#GrandMA2-tutorials\">GrandMA2 tutorials</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"#Misc/other\">Misc/other</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"lighting\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#lighting\" aria-label=\"lighting permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Lighting</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"#Contents\"><code class=\"language-text\">^        back to top        ^</code></a></strong></p>\n<h3 id=\"lighting-software\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#lighting-software\" aria-label=\"lighting software permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Lighting Software</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.avolites.com/software/downloads/titan-pc-suite\">Avolites Titan</a> - PC version of the Titan software which runs on the Avolites desk. Free to use until version 11.4 although it spits out random data once in a while. Requires a dongle from version 12. <code class=\"language-text\">⚠ not free</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://chamsyslighting.com/\">Chamsys MagicQ</a> - MagiQ is a professional lighting software providing up to 64 Artnet universes for free. It includes powerful features like 2D/3D pixel mapping, effect generator, media server and visualizer.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.daslight.com/\">Daslight</a> - DMX lighting software for PC and Mac.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.malighting.com/downloads/products/dot2/\">Dot2 software</a> - Free, offline software for the Dot2 consoles. Includes Dot2 onPC and Dot2 3D.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.etcconnect.com/Products/Consoles/Eos-Family/\">EOS Family</a> - Software for ETC's EOS-family consoles. <code class=\"language-text\">⚠ freemium</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.freestylerdmx.be/\">Freestyler</a> - Free lightning control software</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.malighting.com/downloads/products/grandma2/\">GrandMA2 software</a> - Free, offline software for the GrandMA2 lighting console. Includes GrandMA2 OnPC and MA3D. Does not output DMX for free. <code class=\"language-text\">⚠ freemium</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.malighting.com/downloads/products/grandma3/\">GrandMA3 software</a> - Free, offline software for the <strong>new</strong> GrandMA3 lighting console. Includes GrandMA3 OnPC. Does not output DMX for free. <code class=\"language-text\">⚠ freemium</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.highend.com/products/consoles/\">Hog 4 software</a> - Free, offline software for the Hog 4 lighting console. Includes Hog 4 pc. Does not output DMX for free. <code class=\"language-text\">⚠ freemium</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://obsidiancontrol.com/onyx\">ONYX</a> - Modern lighting control system with alot of features.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.qlcplus.org/\">QLC+</a> - QLC+ is a free and cross-platform software to control DMX or analog lighting systems like moving heads, dimmers, scanners etc. <a href=\"https://github.com/mcallegari/qlcplus\">Source Code</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/mcallegari/qlcplus\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">475</span></span></a> <code class=\"language-text\">✓ open-source</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://xlights.org/\">xLights</a> - Meant for home Christmas light shows but is a great way to sync lights to music on a budget. <a href=\"https://github.com/smeighan/xLights\">Source Code</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/smeighan/xLights\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">236</span></span></a> <code class=\"language-text\">✓ open-source</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"visualizers\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#visualizers\" aria-label=\"visualizers permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Visualizers</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.capture.se/\">Capture</a> - Documentation and visualisation software. Capture is a native macOS and Windows application that lets you work with lighting, video, laser, moving scenery and water effects. Does have a free Student Edition. <code class=\"language-text\">⚠ freemium</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.syncronorm.com/products/depence2/overview/\">Depence²</a> - Depence² is a unique application, which combines the design and visualization process with the potential to control the real show. <code class=\"language-text\">⚠ not free</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.malighting.com/downloads/products/grandma2/\">Ma3D</a> - <strong>Free</strong> lighting visualizer for GrandMA consoles/software.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://cast-soft.com/wysiwyg-lighting-design/\">wysiwyg</a> - wysiwyg is an all-in-one lighting design software with fully integrated CAD, plots, data, visualization and virtual show control. <code class=\"language-text\">⚠ not free</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"audio\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#audio\" aria-label=\"audio permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Audio</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"#Contents\"><code class=\"language-text\">^        back to top        ^</code></a></strong></p>\n<h3 id=\"audio-software\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#audio-software\" aria-label=\"audio software permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Audio Software</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.audacityteam.org/\">Audacity</a> - Audio file editor and analysis tool, great for cropping down sound effects and music tracks. <code class=\"language-text\">✓ open-source</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://ardour.org/\">Ardour</a> - A full realtime audio recording and editing suite. <a href=\"https://github.com/Ardour/ardour\">Source Code</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Ardour/ardour\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">2k</span></span></a> <code class=\"language-text\">✓ open-source</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.da-share.com/software/multiplay/\">da-Share MultiPlay</a> - MultiPlay is a Windows based program designed to play audio cues for theatre or corporate use. It is free to use.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.linux-show-player.org/\">Linux Show Player</a> - Free cue player designed for stage productions. <a href=\"https://github.com/FrancescoCeruti/linux-show-player\">Source Code</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/FrancescoCeruti/linux-show-player\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">113</span></span></a> <code class=\"language-text\">✓ open-source</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://qlab.app/\">QLab</a> - QLab is sound, video, and lighting control for macOS. <code class=\"language-text\">⚠ freemium</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.reaper.fm/\">REAPER</a> - REAPER is a complete digital audio production application for computers, offering a full multitrack audio and MIDI recording, editing, processing, mixing and mastering toolset. <code class=\"language-text\">⚠ freemium</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"audio-tools\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#audio-tools\" aria-label=\"audio tools permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Audio tools</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.artalabs.hr/\">ARTA</a> - A collection of programs for audio measurements and analysis.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.roomeqwizard.com/\">REW</a> - REW is free room acoustics analysis software for measuring and analysing room and loudspeaker responses. Free SMAART alternative.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"video\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#video\" aria-label=\"video permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Video</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"#Contents\"><code class=\"language-text\">^        back to top        ^</code></a></strong></p>\n<p>See <a href=\"https://github.com/ebu/awesome-broadcasting#readme\">ebu/awesome-broadcasting</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ebu/awesome-broadcasting#readme\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1k</span></span></a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"tools\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#tools\" aria-label=\"tools permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Tools</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"#Contents\"><code class=\"language-text\">^        back to top        ^</code></a></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Netlob/livescript\">Livescript</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Netlob/livescript\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">4</span></span></a> - Insert a musical/theatre-script from Google Docs and use this for a live \"autocue\" and scroller with everyone on the site. <code class=\"language-text\">✓ open-source</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://notelek.com/StageClock/\">StageClock</a> - StageClock is a Java based graphical timekeeping application. It outputs a clean feed from an attached monitor, and has time/date, timer, and show information. <code class=\"language-text\">⚠ freemium</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"cads\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#cads\" aria-label=\"cads permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>CADs</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.autodesk.com/products/autocad\">AutoCAD</a> - AutoCAD® is computer-aided design (CAD) software that architects, engineers, and construction professionals rely on to create precise 2D and 3D drawings. <code class=\"language-text\">⚠ not free</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.vectorworks.net/\">Vectorworks</a> - Vectorworks is a versatile, on-premise application that provides extensive 2D drafting, 3D modeling, BIM and rendering capabilities for your architectural and landscape design needs. Also had a special entertainment version: <a href=\"https://www.vectorworks.net/en-GB/spotlight\">Vectorworks Spotlight</a>. <code class=\"language-text\">⚠ not free</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"timecode\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#timecode\" aria-label=\"timecode permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Timecode</h3>\n<p>Timecode is a sequence of numeric codes generated at regular intervals by a timing synchronization system. Timecode is used in video production, show control and other applications which require temporal coordination or logging of recording or actions.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://elteesee.pehrhovey.net/\">El-Tee-See</a> - LTC wav file generator.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/dimitriCGNL/TCGenerator\">TCgenerator</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/dimitriCGNL/TCGenerator\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">2</span></span></a> - Reaper time marker to GrandMA2 TC Generator. <code class=\"language-text\">✓ open-source</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/MrExplode/Timecode\">Timecode</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/MrExplode/Timecode\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">14</span></span></a> - ArtNet and LTC timecode generator, made with Java. <code class=\"language-text\">✓ open-source</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/TheGreyDiamond/Time-MIDI-sender\">Time MIDI sender</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/TheGreyDiamond/Time-MIDI-sender\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">0</span></span></a> - A free tool for sending time data to DasLight (via MIDI). <code class=\"language-text\">✓ open-source</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://timelord-mtc.com/\">TimelordMTC</a> - Advanced timecode management tool. <code class=\"language-text\">⚠ not free</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/lorenzofattori/M2Q\">M2Q</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/lorenzofattori/M2Q\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">3</span></span></a> - Python application capable to trigger Chamsys Consoles/Software via MIDI for advanced synchronized shows. <code class=\"language-text\">✓ open-source</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"monitoring\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#monitoring\" aria-label=\"monitoring permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Monitoring</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/zjstraus/AES67-WebMeter\">AES67 WebMeter</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/zjstraus/AES67-WebMeter\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">4</span></span></a> - Server that receives an AES67 audio stream and presents a webpage with meters. <code class=\"language-text\">✓ open-source</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/x42/meters.lv2\">meters.lv2</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/x42/meters.lv2\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">123</span></span></a> - meters.lv2 is a collection of audio-level meters with GUI in LV2 plugin format. <code class=\"language-text\">✓ open-source</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://opensoundmeter.com/\">Open Sound Meter</a> - Clean, open-source sound meter. Supports RTA, magnitude, phase and impulse response, coherence, group delay and more. <code class=\"language-text\">✓ open-source</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"libraries-and-frameworks\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#libraries-and-frameworks\" aria-label=\"libraries and frameworks permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Libraries and frameworks</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"#Contents\"><code class=\"language-text\">^        back to top        ^</code></a></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.openlighting.org/ola/\">Open Lighting Architecture</a> - A framework for lighting control information. Supports a range of protocols and over a dozen of USB devices. <a href=\"https://github.com/OpenLightingProject/ola\">Source Code</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/OpenLightingProject/ola\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">429</span></span></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/node-dmx/dmx\">node-dmx</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/node-dmx/dmx\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">200</span></span></a> - DMX controller library for Node.js. <code class=\"language-text\">nodejs</code> <code class=\"language-text\">✓ open-source</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"artnet-libraries\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#artnet-libraries\" aria-label=\"artnet libraries permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>ArtNet Libraries</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/hobbyquaker/artnet\">artnet</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/hobbyquaker/artnet\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">94</span></span></a> - Node.js module that can be used to send ArtDMX packages to an Art-Net node. <code class=\"language-text\">nodejs</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/cansik/artnet4j\">artnet4j</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/cansik/artnet4j\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">51</span></span></a> - Art-Net library for Java and Processing. <code class=\"language-text\">java</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"hardware\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#hardware\" aria-label=\"hardware permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Hardware</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"#Contents\"><code class=\"language-text\">^        back to top        ^</code></a></strong></p>\n<p>See <a href=\"https://github.com/stingalleman/awesome-audiovisual/blob/main/HARDWARE.md\">HARDWARE.md</a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"graphics\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#graphics\" aria-label=\"graphics permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Graphics</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"#Contents\"><code class=\"language-text\">^        back to top        ^</code></a></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.gimp.org/\">GIMP</a> - GIMP is a cross-platform image editor available for Linux, Windows, and macOS.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://inkscape.org/\">Inkscape</a> - Inkscape is a professional vector graphics editor for Linux, Windows and macOS.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"resources\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#resources\" aria-label=\"resources permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Resources</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"#Contents\"><code class=\"language-text\">^        back to top        ^</code></a></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/chamsys.users/\">Chamsys Programmers and Users facebook group</a> - The best place to find information about Chamsys consoles and software.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCdLor-EVzOjOY7OZNXt8eIw\">Christian Jackson</a> - YouTube channel about concert lighting. Also has great MA tutorials.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://tsp.esta.org/tsp/documents/published_docs.php\">ESTA Technical Standards Program</a> - Collection of technical standards in the entertainment technology industry.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://geezersofgear.libsyn.com/\">Geezers of Gear</a> - Entertainment Production Industry veteran talking about pro-audio, lighting, staging, video + the people and companies who work in this great industry.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/limelightwired/\">@limelightwired</a> - Lighting production community on Instagram.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/nodiscc/awesome-linuxaudio\">awesome-linuxaudio</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/nodiscc/awesome-linuxaudio\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">779</span></span></a> - A Awesome list with all things Linux audio.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://qlab.app/cookbook/\">QLab Cookbook</a> - The cookbook is a collection of projects, examples, and experiments using a broad range of QLab programming techniques including AppleScript, OSC, external control using QLab Remote, third-party MIDI and OSC controllers, and other software.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://reddit.com/r/lightingdesign/\">/r/lightingdesign</a> - The Reddit community for lighting designers worldwide.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://reddit.com/r/techtheatre/\">/r/techtheatre</a> - The reddit community for all production designers and technicians!</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"blogs\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#blogs\" aria-label=\"blogs permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Blogs</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.mikewoodld.com/blog/\">mikewoodld.com/blog/</a> - Blog of Lighting Designer Mike Wood.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://notelek.com/blog/\">notelek.com/blog/</a> - LXR Stage Technology Blog.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"tutorials\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#tutorials\" aria-label=\"tutorials permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Tutorials</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"#Contents\"><code class=\"language-text\">^        back to top        ^</code></a></strong></p>\n<h3 id=\"grandma2-tutorials\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#grandma2-tutorials\" aria-label=\"grandma2 tutorials permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>GrandMA2 tutorials</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lhYDUzWKz3M\">GMA2 colour picker tutorial</a> - A tutorial for how to add a colour picker in GrandMA2.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"miscother\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#miscother\" aria-label=\"miscother permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Misc/other</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"#Contents\"><code class=\"language-text\">^        back to top        ^</code></a></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/BryanCrotaz/blender-artnet\">Blender ArtNet</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/BryanCrotaz/blender-artnet\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">14</span></span></a> - Blender script to push ArtNet data to Evee lights. Runs at 30fps with Evee rendering in the viewport. <code class=\"language-text\">✓ open-source</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linux\">Linux</a> - A free operating system that can run on pretty much every kind of computer and is great for breathing new life into old computers that aren't supported by the newer Windows editions. There's tons of different distributions to choose from,. The most common one for general computer stuff is <a href=\"https://ubuntu.com/\">Ubuntu</a>. <code class=\"language-text\">✓ open-source</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/cbdevnet/midimonster/\">MIDI Monster</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/cbdevnet/midimonster/\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">253</span></span></a> - MIDIMonster is a universal control and translation tool. It can translate between many different protocols such as MIDI, Artnet, sACN and OSC. <code class=\"language-text\">✓ open-source</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.usedlighting.com/\">UsedLighting</a> - Marketplace for buying/selling used lighting hardware.</li>\n</ul>","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#awesome-audiovisual-awesome\">Awesome Audiovisual <img src=\"https://awesome.re/badge.svg\" alt=\"Awesome\"></a></p>\n<ul>\n<li